content.description: Nice little problem (sit start) that follows a crack system and even has a sloper/jug.  It's on the side of the CAB boulder facing away from the lake.  It's on the right side when looking at the CAB boulder with the lake behind it.
Climb the arete (stand start) to the right of CAB (the face climb on the tallest face on the CAB boulder).
To the left of the arete near the water (called Pho).  Climb up a small crack system (stand start) on the face on good holds.

remind yourself just how small of holds you need to climb a vertical face with this problem. Climb the face 5 feet to the left of the tall arete. Watch out, you'll be topping out above the pile of rock on your left, a fall would definitely result in a twisted ankle.        start on 2 good holds and good feet, then make 2 static movements onto a slopey crimp then a very small horn with a thumb catch. top out slightly left above the rock pile.
content.location: 5 to 7 feet left of the arete. this climb resides on the beach side of the boulder.

content.description: To the right of Pho (the short arete near the lake), this climb (sit start) goes up  the face following crimpy holds to a small diagonal crack and then the top out.
Climb arete on crimps, stand start
Climb the easy arete (directly across from the Nice Boulder but the one farthest away from the lake).  Sit start.

Climb the tall obvious arete of CAB boulder. Decent rock quality (relative) awaits but check before committing because there is a nasty landing below. Start down and right of the arete, move left and up as you climb the arete.
content.protection: Lots of pads, spotter and nerves of steal.
content.location: Climb the obvious arete of CAB boulder

content.description: start on a good jug down and right from the tall arete. Work your way up the face using the 2 vertical seems.
content.location: On CAB boulder, start bottom right of the face that is on the right side of the arete. When you walk down to the beach/pier and look to your right, this will be the first face you see.

content.description: A tall and vertical boulder that faces the beach and the pier. There are a couple very decent problems on this boulder worth checking out with decent rock quality.         Receive sun in the morning to afternoon then shade in the evening.
